item.title: Ufo
item.dc:creator: @Andrew_Ferguson The317Guy
item.description:
@Andrew_Ferguson wrote:

[quote=“mihalich, post:15, topic:402229”][quote author=Andrew Ferguson link=topic=499284.msg3651301#msg3651301 date=1309749050]
Looks like two Lockheed U-2’s, they are most likely flying over head for visibility readings, they do this when the weather is rather hot to check visibility for flight conditions the following morning. Nothing to worry about its not a UFO, moving to slowly and both lights are in the standard flight formation (one behind the other, they aren’t meant to fly side by side because of the decreased visibility of the other, also you may notice the one in the back is flying lower so it can see the one above it better). (Sibling is a fighter jet pilot.)
[/quote]
Would we be able to hear them fly by tho? That was the only thing that made it really stand out to me not hearing anything and just seeing the lights go over.

Btw I’m leaning towards them being lanterns thanks to xryz[/quote]
No you wouldn’t, they are stealth planes and are used during night because of their low win-resistance and their ability to fly through most weather. Only part you would really hear is the take off if your within 1-2 miles.

Read full topic

item.title: Ufo
item.dc:creator: @CoonHunter CoonHunter
item.description:
@CoonHunter wrote:

UFO = Unidentified Flying Object - Not to be confused with Alien Spaceship. (damn mexicans, lol jk <3)

Probably a couple satellites in the sky. I saw 3 last night personally that were moving fairly quickly, only real excuse I can think of. Although I was at a rodeo last night as well, so I could of been seeing things (bright lights + outdoors at 11PM = seeing spots). Anyways, It is very possible it was a U2 plane, as these were originally build for stealth and spying during the cold war (could be wrong, if so blame my history teacher) as mentioned checking for visibility or of the such. Nothing to be worried about nonetheless.
